caption.text: Ok, the fact this post even had to happen is insulting, but I don't take being called "fake" lightly. And, I'm sure it wasn't a compliment.  If you've ever talked to me and/or have followed me long, you'd know I love the IG community. I appreciate the support, encouragement and inspiration you all have given me, and always hope I have those aspects to offer you all as well. Through photos we share ourselves and our lives. There's a sort of intimacy in that that grows trust and friendship amongst strangers. Don't you think? With that said, it's sad when it only takes one person to ruin that.  Now, I know most of you don't fit into the category of rude, and I know I shouldn't let one person bother me, but it does when it's my work - my integrity - that's being questioned. And to have to even prove anything to anyone is beyond appalling. However, I'm not one to back down when I'm being called out, especially since I've done nothing wrong. So, here it is... the process - or what I remember of it - of the last pic. Keep in mind, as some of you already know, I don't keep notes on my edits but I do my best to let people know the process I went through to get the pic if they ask nicely and without accusation.  I started with the original then used the cross process filter in camera +. I either used clarity or sharpen to sharpen the image. I then went into Iris and solarized it. After that I just used different filters until I got the colors I wanted and voila. I couldn't decide which one I liked best so I diptic'd it and the final product is the one you see.   I hope this clears things up. And know I'm trying really hard not to be immature and say fucktard... but yeah.
